description.en: The ODRL Vocabulary and Expression defines a set of concepts and terms (the vocabulary) and encoding mechanism (the expression) for permissions and obligations statements describing digital content usage based on the ODRL Information Model.

comments.en: This is the RDF ontology for ODRL Version 2.2.

contributor.value: W3C Permissions & Obligations Expression Working Group

note.value: Instances of the LeftOperand class are used as the leftOperand of a Constraint.

definition.value: Left operand for a constraint expression.
A boolean expression that refines the semantics of an Action and Party/Asset Collection or declare the conditions applicable to a Rule.

note.value: Instances of the Operator class representing relational operators.

definition.value: Operator for constraint expression.

note.value: Actions may be allowed by Permissions, disallowed by Prohibitions, or made mandatory by Duties.

definition.value: An operation on an Asset.

note.value: A Request Policy  MUST contain a target Asset, a Party with Assignee function, and at least one of a Permission or Prohibition rule. The Request MAY also contain the Party with Assigner function if this is known. No privileges are granted to any Party.

definition.value: A Policy that proposes a Rule over an Asset from an assignee.

note.value: A Policy may contain multiple Rules.

definition.value: A non-empty group of Permissions and/or Prohibitions.
The obligation to perform an Action

note.value: Instances of the RightOperand class are used as the rightOperand of a Constraint.

definition.value: Right operand for constraint expression.

note.value: Rule is an abstract concept.

definition.value: An abstract concept that represents the common characteristics of Permissions, Prohibitions, and Duties.
The ability to perform an Action over an Asset.

note.value: A Privacy Policy  MUST contain a target Asset, a Party with Assigner  is, a Party with Assignee function, and at least one of a Permission or Prohibition rule that MUST include a Duty. The target Asset SHOULD contain or relate to personal information about the Assignee. The Duty MUST describe obligations on the Assigner about managing the Asset. The Assignee is being granted the terms of the Privacy policy from the Assigner.

definition.value: A Policy that expresses a Rule over an Asset containing personal information.

note.value: The Party entity could be a person, group of people, organisation, or agent. An agent is a person or thing that takes an active role or produces a specified effect. To describe more details about the Party, it is recommended to use W3C vCard Ontology [[vcard-rdf]] or FOAF Vocabulary [[foaf]].

definition.value: An entity or a collection of entities that undertake Roles in a Rule.

note.value: An Agreement Policy MUST contain at least one Permission or Prohibition rule, a Party with Assigner function, and a Party with Assignee function (in the same Permission or Prohibition). The Agreement Policy will grant the terms of the Policy from the Assigner to the Assignee.

definition.value: A Policy that grants the assignee a Rule over an Asset from an assigner.
The inability to perform an Action over an Asset.
A logical expression that refines the semantics of an Action and Party/Asset Collection or declare the conditions applicable to a Rule.

note.value: The Asset entity can be any form of identifiable resource, such as data/information, content/media, applications, or services. Furthermore, it can be used to represent other Asset entities that are needed to undertake the Policy expression, such as with the Duty entity. To describe more details about the Asset, it is recommended to use Dublin Core [[dcterms]] elements or other content metadata.

definition.value: A resource or a collection of resources that are the subject of a Rule.

note.value: The remedy property expresses an agreed Duty that must be fulfilled in case that a Prohibition has been violated by being exercised.

definition.value: Relates an individual remedy Duty to a Prohibition.

note.value: A Duty is a pre-condition which must be fulfilled in order to receive the Permission.

definition.value: Relates an individual Duty to a Permission.
Relates an individual Permission to a Policy.
The operator function applied to operands of a Constraint

note.value: The Duty is a requirement which must be fulfilled.

definition.value: Relates an individual Duty to a Policy.

note.value: When used with set-based operators, a list of values may be used.

definition.value: The value of the right operand in a constraint expression.

note.value: The purpose is to explicitly assert that the semantics of the referenced instance of an other Action encompasses (includes) the semantics of this instance of Action. The includedIn property is transitive, and as such, the Actions form ancestor relationships.

definition.value: An Action transitively asserts that another Action that encompasses its operational semantics.
The target property indicates the Asset that is the primary subject to which the Rule action directly applies.
The output property specifies the Asset which is created from the output of the Action.

note.value: Sub-properties of operand are used for Logical Constraints.

definition.value: Operand is an abstract property for a logical relationship.

note.value: The consequence property is utilised to express the repercussions of not fulfilling an agreed Policy obligation or duty for a Permission. If either of these fails to be fulfilled, then this will result in the consequence Duty also becoming a new requirement, meaning that the original obligation or duty, as well as the consequence Duty must all be fulfilled

definition.value: Relates a Duty to another Duty, the latter being a consequence of not fulfilling the former.

note.value: The child policy will inherit Rules from the parent policy

definition.value: Relates a (child) policy to another (parent) policy from which terms are inherited.
The left operand in a constraint expression.
Relates an individual Prohibition to a Policy.
The operation relating to the Asset for which the Rule is being subjected.

note.value: The parent property to sub-properties that express explicit failure contexts.

definition.value: Failure is an abstract property that defines the violation (or unmet) relationship between Rules.
The Party is the issuer of the Rule.

note.value: In RDF encodings, use of the rdf:datatype MUST be used. In JSON-LD encoding, the use of @type MUST be used.

definition.value: The datatype of the value of the rightOperand or rightOperandReference of a Constraint.
The Party is the recipient of the Rule.

note.value: The property asserts that an instance of Action entails that the other instance of Action is not prohibited.

definition.value: An Action asserts that another Action is not prohibited to enable its operational semantics.

note.value: Example: the Action print is only permitted on 50% of the asset.

definition.value: Constraint used to refine the semantics of an Action, or Party/Asset Collection

note.value: Constraints on Rules are used to determine if a rule is Active or not. Example: the Permission rule is only active during the year 2018.

definition.value: Constraint applied to a Rule
